Title: The Show Must Go On
Description: Gather Black Pigment from Black Fungus around Ebonscale Reach for Magistrate Redridge.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: We were betrayed by the Dynasty Empress, but we've adapted - we've learned that the secret is not forgetting what makes us human.\n\nThat's why practicing the arts remains one of our highest priorities.
InProgressResponse: I do think the fungus will make for an excellent ink.\n\nThis is the only way we can pull off the production.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, perfect! I'll start mixing the ink right away, and then I can recopy my script for 'The Empress's Journey'.\n\nI realize what a trifle this must seem in the face of the Corrupted, but we must follow through.

Title: Statuette Stash
Description: Collect four Dragon Statuettes to deliver to Zeng Lingyun in Ebonscale so she can locate the dock leading to the Empress's fleet.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Yes. Her thirst for power overcame her sense of respect and decorum. It is a tragic tale.\n\nThe past is gone, however, and it is the present for which I am now concerned. The Empress is a threat to the entire world.
InProgressResponse: The dragon statuettes are the only way to gain access to the Empress's docks.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, thank you. Empress Taiying fancies herself a dragon goddess, but she is only a human who has succumbed to Corruption.\n\nWith you as our champion, I believe we can bring her down for good.

Title: End of Her Reign (Expedition)
Description: Enter the boat in the Dynasty Fortress, sail to the Dynasty Port, defeat Dynasty Captains and destroy her ships, and then defeat Empress Zhou Taiying herself. Then report back to Zeng Lingyun in the Ebonscale Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: You will find her, and her entire fleet, within the Dynasty Shipyard. I do not know exactly where, so you will have to search inside. \n\nI hope you realize the importance of this - she cannot be permitted to launch that fleet.
InProgressResponse: Whatever it takes, you must destroy Empress Taiying and her foul fleet.\n\nNot just for Aeternum, but for all the world.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, I have heard the news - at last her dark reign has ended.\n\nThank you, Champion. You have put a deeply troubled soul to rest, and in doing so, you may have very well saved the world.

Title: Flower for the Departed
Description: Place a Blossoming Flower on the Altar of the Departed in the Haunted Crypt for Elder Danya in the Ebonscale Reach Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: You must understand - the people here - many have actually been given the comfort of eternal rest. \n\nIt's a blessing after they've endured so much at the hands of the Empress.
InProgressResponse: The Blossoming Flower, for how full of life it is, should help the spirits rest.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Oh, I was just reading a book of Bhakti kaal. Not enough to share I'm afraid.\n\nBut you placed the Blossoming Flower? Did it help the drowned Dynasty citizens find rest?

Title: Ebonscale Alligators
Description: Collect Ebony Scales from Ebonscale Alligators for Survivalist Hopkins in the Ebonscale Reach Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Excellent! Let's make it a competition, then! Who can skin the most Ebonscale Alligators?\n\nThere's a hollow in Moss Mire that teems with them. Gather their scales, and I'll make you a fine new gatorskin satchel.
InProgressResponse: I have to admit that this challenge is not only for the bag and the bragging rights. \n\nThese alligators are a threat - have you ever been drowned and eaten by a gator? It's an experience that haunts you forever.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Impressive! As much as it pains me to say it, you are a better Insti-gator than I am! Heh? You like it? My pun game is as sharp as their teeth.\n\nAs promised, here is your new bag.

Title: Shrine Cleansing (Elite)
Description: Cleanse the Dragon Shrine in the Dynasty Shrine for Artificer Long in the Ebonscale Reach Settlement.
PlayerPrompt: "Is there some way I can help?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Yes. The Dragon Shrine. The Empress and I shared a love for dragons, but she twisted my work into a nexus of evil.\n\nThe Corrupted now use the shrine to conduct foul rituals and concoct dark plans. It must be cleansed.
InProgressResponse: The Dynasty Corrupted are a force to be reckoned with, and they are abetted by Corrupted from the Mainland.\n\nI would not be surprised if you encounter both at the Shrine.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You saw it then? The Shrine I built for her, and what she did to it... overrun with all manner of Corrupted abominations. I was ashamed.\n\nThank for making it right again.

Title: What Makes the Shallows Crimson
Description: Collect samples of life in the Crimson Shallows for Barkeep Bao in the Ebonscale Reach Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: That's the question you can help answer! There are so many unanswered questions on Aeternum - it keeps me awake at night!\n\n If we could just answer this one, I would be happy. What makes the Crimson Shallows crimson?
InProgressResponse: I'll need plants from the area as well as samples from the fauna that eat them. \n\nThank you for assisting me in this endeavor.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Wow, that is a lot of samples! I can certainly find the common element.\n\nI suspect it is an algae-like substance that, when exposed to heat, makes the Shallows red. We will soon find out!

Title: Corrupted Critics
Description: Sabotage and pillage in the Serenity Monastery for Magistrate Redridge in the Ebonscale Reach Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Long ago, the Clifftop Monastery was a place where we could meditate and find solace, but these days, it rings with the din of the Corrupted.\n\nFrom up there, they spy on us and plot to sabotage our initiatives.
InProgressResponse: Please, dearie, do make haste and visit the Clifftop Monastery.\n\nIf the Corrupted learn of our enterprise, they will try to take advantage of that.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Finally, the Corrupted are paid back for spoiling the Monastery. This intelligence will prove useful too. \n\nMost importantly, however, we can now begin our rigorous rehearsal schedule.

Title: Study In Green
Description: Collect Dryad Wood from the Ruins in Moss Mire for Artificer Long in the Ebonscale Reach Settlement.
PlayerPrompt: "Is there some way I can prove it?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Yes, support me in my work defending the settlement. I need materials for the armaments I would forge.\n\nI have the ores, but I need wood for the hafts and stocks. The Wood of the Dryads would be most effective.
InProgressResponse: In her Corrupted madness, Empress Zhou believes she can build a fleet to sail back there, reclaim her throne and dominate with her Corruption across the whole world. Madness, pure madness.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah yes, this Dryad Wood will do nicely. The Angry Earth have a collective magic that is powerful against the Corrupted.\n\nThank you, this will help our settlement be better defended. This proves your heart is pure.

Title: Tiger, Tiger
Description: Defeat Tigers for Trophy Teeth and Defeat Makari at the Tiger Cave for Survivalist Hopkins in the Ebonscale Reach Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Damn straight, the Empress brought them from the old world, but they've evolved here and become even more dangerous. We have a bounty on them.\n\nThunder Cradle's where the Tigers den. Bring me their teeth, and you'll be rewarded.
InProgressResponse: The Tigers were once pets from the Empress's royal menagerie, but they've learned to be free and wild here.\n\nYou'll not a hunt a more dangerous quarry.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Looks like you really earned your stripes! In fact you could say you were absolutely purr-fect! Ha, don't give me that look, you know you love my puns.\n\nAnd here's your reward, master-hunter. You've earned it.

Title: Captain's Orders
Description: Defeat Undead Pirates and obtain the Captain's Puzzlebox for Elder Danya in the Ebonscale Reach Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Perfect, perfect. Then you are familiar with these Lost Pirates - they are plague down there, and here as well.\n\nThey also present us with an opportunity to acquire supplies we cannot get elsewhere.
InProgressResponse: Find the Puzzlebox and recover the manifest within, and then you know what I value most in this world.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You have the manifest? Then you have found me out. \n\nThere is one thing I value in this world more than anything, and that is... Fine literature. Mmm.

Title: Skysong's End
Description: Kill Corrupted forces at Skysong Lagoon to interrupt the Corrupted meeting. Then report back to Artificer Long  in the Ebonscale Reach Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: That is a bold idea, and one which I would normally consider laughable, but you seem… quite capable.\n\nEven you must be careful however; the meeting is set to take place in the Skysong Lagoon Temple.
InProgressResponse: These plans suggest the construction of the Empress's fleet is actually a joint effort now with the Tempest.\n\nDisrupting this meeting at the Temple may be the most important thing we can do.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You did it, didn't you? Marched into the Temple and confronted both the Empress's and the Tempest's followers.\n\nThis is a victory that will go down in Aeternum history. I feel… quite happy about this, as well.

Title: Temple Troubles
Description: Decimate the Corrupted Population of the Dynasty Mountain Temple and take out their leader Legarath. Then report back to Barkeep Bao in the Ebonscale Reach Settlement.
PlayerPrompt: "What sort of task did you have in mind?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: There is a Dynasty Mountain Temple in Thunder Cradle overseen by a Corrupted warrior who goes by the name Legarath.\n\nIf you can bring down him and his Corrupted ilk it would help me greatly.
InProgressResponse: Has Legarath bested you in battle? Please do not give up. I know his skills are nothing to be scoffed at but I sense power in you, too.\n\nPlease dish out justice in a way I cannot.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: So Legarath and the soldiers who followed him into Corruption are defeated. It brings me some solace in the present, but my heart will take time to mend.

Title: Justice For The Dynasty (Expedition)
Description: Obtain Dynasty Shackles from Dynasty Shipyard Lieutenants and return them to Liberator Guo outside the Dynasty Shipyards In Ebonscale.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: You stand at the precipice of an operation that is centuries in the making. \n\nThe people of Zhou Taiying's Dynasty have been betrayed by her in her turn to Corruption.
InProgressResponse: Taking these shackles away from the upper members of her court give adventurers and innocents a fighting chance in running from Taiying's terror.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: These devices are truly the tools of an oppressor.\n\nThank you for bringing them to me so I can melt down and repurpose them into something for the good of the people of the Dynasty.

Title: The Last Argument
Description: Help Wang Tangzhi and Alvaro de Villanueva construct their masterpiece Blunderbuss.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Excellent! This will require materials of the highest quality. But you don’t strike me as someone who’d shy away from a bit of danger to acquire them. \nAh, such a weapon we’ll craft for you. It will be the pinnacle of our work!

Title: A Stock of Ironwood
Description: Travel to Edengrove and acquire the ingredients needed to prepare a stock for the Blunderbuss.

Title: Polished to a Shine
Description: Prepare and craft the Hardened Ironwood Planks for Alvaro to craft the stock.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: And so it begins. I requested regular Ironwood, not treated with whatever this is. I'll need to revise the measurements, conduct pressure and stress testing... \n\nI just hope that it hasn't changed the structure too terribly.

Title: A Precision Lock
Description: Travel to Reekwater and seek out the components needed to complete the lock of the Blunderbuss.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: What we need will be dangerous to acquire. The pirates in Reekwater have flintlock pistols of unique make. That’s what we need. Get some of those weapons if you can. We'll also need slivers of platinum, freshly mined.

Title: Handcrafted to Perfection
Description: Craft the final pieces of the Blunderbuss lock using the recovered components.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: I knew this would happen! No critique of your abilities, just on the changes he's made to the design itself. \n\nThese hard lines, a complete lack of style. This doesn’t stand out! A wielder would take no pride in showing this off!

Title: A Receiver Most Elegant
Description: Fill the receiver with azoth powder and gold, found throughout Aeternum.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: The azoth, yes. The catalyst? Flakes of pure gold will be just fine, actually, and straight from a fresh vein. \n\nOnce you have the azoth and gold sealed within the receiver, it will require a... field test.

Title: Quenched in Darkness
Description: Test the receiver's durability by assaulting Corruption Breaches throughout Aeternum.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse:
Finished with the receiver, have you? 

Hrm... internals are a bit overdesigned. Could've used a different metal for the frame. Seals could be a bit thicker, too... 

Well, I suppose it'll have to do.

Title: Barrels of Unerring Accuracy
Description: Collect the components needed to reforce the barrels of the Blunderbuss.
ObjectiveProposalResponse:
Hold on now! You won't catch me carving fire-breathing dragons on my barrels! Or adding gilded inlay to my stocks! 

But perhaps some of my designs could be improved upon, be a bit less severe. 

And speaking of barrels…
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Good, good! Yes, let me see the... hmm… \n\nYou know, seeing these pieces together, there is something poetic about it all: the raw austerity of his designs, paired with my artistry... quite a pleasant duality to the work.

Title: Ignition of Sublime Flame
Description: Obtain the ingredients needed for the Gunpowder Additive, then craft it and deliver it to Alvaro.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: The Corrupted gunners at the base of Shattered Mountain use a strange form of charcoal for their gunpowder. \n\nAlvaro discovered that mixing this strange charcoal with regular gunpowder would produce an even stronger force!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You have the mixture! Let me give it a taste... Tastes as foul as I remember, but in the right proportions! \n\nTangzhi and I have assembled everything. I just need to get this seated in the receiver, and we should be set.
